<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>VT 365 Diesel Engine - 2004 Model Year - ELECTRONICALLY CONTROLLED VARIABLE GEOMETRY TURBOCHARGER (VGT) -
        Removal - VGT and Components
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="s26502.2.3" graphiccount="14">
        <title>VGT and Components</title>
        <figure id="f2650205" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD13/D13143.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Air inlet duct</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Lube oil fill extension tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet duct</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet duct clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil fill extension tube and put a cap in the oil fill hole of the valve cover to keep
                out foreign material.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650205" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1546.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Air inlet duct</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Turbo air inlet</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet duct</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet duct clamp</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the air inlet duct clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove air inlet duct and clamp. Put a cap over the opening of the VGT air inlet, to keep
                out foreign material.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650206" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1545.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Breather tube and pitot tube</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet duct</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Breather hose</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Pitot tube</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove air inlet duct breather hose by turning breather hose and pitot tube enough to align
                hold clips with opening, to remove from the crankcase breather cover.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put caps in the opening of the breather cover vent hole, to keep out foreign material.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650207" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD15/D15101.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil supply tube to VGT</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolt (2)</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two M8 x 20 bolts from the oil supply tube mounted on top of the VGT and swing oil
                supply tube out of the way.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil supply tube gasket and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put a cap over oil supply inlet to the VGT, to keep out foreign material.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650208" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD15/D15102.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil supply tube for VGT to oil cooler cover assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Oil supply tube</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolt</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect oil supply tube from engine by removing the M8 x 20 flange head bolt.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove oil supply tube from oil cooler cover assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650210" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figD15/D15103.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Exhaust adapter V-clamp for VGT</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove exhaust adapter V-clamp.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cover all openings to the VGT when piping is removed, to keep out foreign material.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650211" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1551b.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Center mounting bolt and spacer for VGT</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M8 x 30 flange head bolt and spacer securing the VGT to the center of mounting
                bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650212" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1551a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Rear mounting bolt for VGT</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove M8 x 30 flange head bolt securing the VGT to the rear of mounting bracket.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650213" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1552.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Front mounting bolt and spacer for VGT</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove one M8 x 30 flange head bolt and spacer securing the VGT to the front of mounting
                bracket.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>If removing the VGT only, cap off oil drain line to keep out foreign material.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift the VGT assembly up and off the engine. Make sure all openings in the VGT assembly are
                capped.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Use Compressor Inlet Cap and Exhaust Outlet Cap. . If plastic caps are not available, cover
                    openings with tape.
                </para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2650214" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1549.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Oil drain tube for VGT</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f2650215" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1549a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removal of oil drain tube for VGT</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Pull oil drain tube out of high-pressure oil pump cover.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Put a cap over opening in the high-pressure oil pump cover to keep out foreign material.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove two O-rings on the oil drain tube and discard.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650216" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1550.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>VGT bracket bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f2650217" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1550a.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Removal of VGT bracket bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove four M8 x 20 VGT bracket bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650218" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd15/d1553.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                     scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
            <caption>VGT mounting bracket</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift up the left side of the bracket first so the right side can clear the EGR cooler
                coolant inlet tube.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
